<nyne-vfs>

This codebase is mounted through **nyne**, a FUSE virtual filesystem. Every source file has an `@/` companion namespace exposing decomposed symbols, LSP intelligence, and git history as virtual files. **Use `@/` paths instead of raw file reads/edits.** This is not optional — nyne enables maximum accuracy and minimal token consumption, and ensures only relevant information enters the conversation context.

## Quick Reference

| Task | Operation |
|-|-|
| Explore a file | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md` |
| Read a symbol body | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo.{{ ext }}` |
| Read just the signature | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/signature.{{ ext }}` |
| Edit a symbol | `Edit file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}` |
| Delete a symbol | `Bash: rmdir file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/` |
| Rename a symbol (LSP) | `Bash: mv file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old@/ file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/new@/` |
| Find callers | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/CALLERS.md` |
| Find dependencies | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DEPS.md` |
| Find all references | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/REFERENCES.md` |
| Check diagnostics | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/DIAGNOSTICS.md` |
| Apply a code action | `Bash: patch -p1 < file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff` |
| Explore a directory | `Read src/dispatch@/OVERVIEW.md` |

## Core Rules

1. **Start with OVERVIEW.md.** Always read the symbol table before diving into code.
2. **Read CALLERS.md before modifying.** Understand blast radius before changing any function or type.
3. **Proactively check `actions/` for LSP actions**.
4. **Follow symlinks.** `callers/`, `deps/`, `references/` link to other symbols' `@/` directories — read, edit, and inspect actions through them without resolving file paths.

## Advanced Workflows — Load Skills

The quick reference above covers common operations. For advanced workflows, load the relevant skill:

- `/nyne-navigate` — line ranges, markdown sections, by-kind filtering, token budgeting, edit staging
- `/nyne-analyze` — git blame/log per-symbol, definition/declaration lookup, call chain traversal, code action diffs
